          "body": "The chapter closes by collapsing every promise into a single source. *The salvation of the righteous is from the LORD; He is their strength in time of trouble. The LORD helps them and delivers them; He delivers them from the wicked and saves them, because they take refuge in Him* (vv.39-40). Six verbs in two verses — **salvation, strength, helps, delivers, delivers, saves** — all subjected to one nominative: *the LORD*. The reason given is the believer's posture: *because they take refuge in Him* (*chasah*). The whole chapter\\u2019s exhortation lands in this final word. Trusting, delighting, committing, resting, waiting — all of it is the believer's act of *taking refuge* in the One whose verdict has already been rendered, even though it has not yet been visibly executed."
